 Episode 2 

53
00:05:08,470 --> 00:05:11,980
- Hello?
 -  Hello, this is T Hotel. 

54
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:17,650
- Ms. Oh, please show her where she needs to go.
 - Yes, Doctor.

55
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:19,800
- Please take care.
 - Thank you.

56
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:26,900
 This is T Hotel. 

57
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:31,220
 Your check-in is after 3:00 p.m. on Friday. 

58
00:05:48,590 --> 00:05:50,180
Yes?

59
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:55,070
Attorney Cha.

60
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:59,030
Kim Min Jeong and Kim Jun Hui are in the lobby for their scheduled consultations.

61
00:05:59,030 --> 00:06:01,180
Oh, is that so?

62
00:06:01,980 --> 00:06:04,230
Should I take them to the VIP consultation room?

63
00:06:04,230 --> 00:06:06,200
You said their property value is high, right?

64
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:10,600
The litigation opponent of the plaintiff, Kim Min Jeong, owns about six billion won.

65
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:13,920
He's the son of the Assemblyman Park Hyeok Sae.

66
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:18,010
Park Hyeok Sae, who raised a controversy regarding gifting to his son?

67
00:06:18,010 --> 00:06:19,240
Yes, that's right.

68
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:22,260
We'll need to take a lot from him in the property division.

69
00:06:22,260 --> 00:06:25,200
You can take them to the VIP consultation office and...

70
00:06:27,190 --> 00:06:30,300
Please tell Attorney Han Yu Ri to come up.

71
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:34,000
Don't you always take VIP cases alone?

72
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:36,150
You said there are two plaintiffs.

73
00:06:36,150 --> 00:06:38,430
Send up Attorney Han Yu Ri.

74
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:40,520
Yes.

75
00:07:03,550 --> 00:07:05,640
At first, I didn't even suspect them.

76
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:08,970
-  It's snowing.  
- It's your favorite snow, Min Jeong.

77
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:12,170
Should we buy more and take some when we go camping with Jun Hui's family?

78
00:07:12,170 --> 00:07:13,540
That sounds lovely.

79
00:07:13,540 --> 00:07:16,950
Boss, please give us five servings of tteokbokki (rice cakes with chili sauce) to go.

80
00:07:16,950 --> 00:07:19,220
- Yes.
 - Thanks.

81
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:23,530
I'm so glad you introduced Jun Hui's family to me.

82
00:07:23,530 --> 00:07:26,020
The kids get along so well.

83
00:07:27,170 --> 00:07:31,620
To think I'd get so deeply close with my wife's friend since middle school...

84
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:33,180
I'm thankful to you, Oppa.

85
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:37,770
Other husbands would hate it if their wives asked them to go places with their male friend's family.

86
00:07:37,770 --> 00:07:39,630
Why? I love it so much.

87
00:07:39,630 --> 00:07:42,780
Jun Hui's so good to me, calling me "hyeongnim."

88
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:53,700
Man, it's so cold.

89
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:55,350
It's cold, right?

90
00:07:56,310 --> 00:07:58,380
Right, your seatbelt.

91
00:08:05,150 --> 00:08:07,750
 But that bitch's handprint... 

92
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:11,910
 We sleep in separate rooms because I snore. 

93
00:08:11,910 --> 00:08:13,720
Aigoo, it's cold.

94
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:16,290
 That's when I should've known. 

95
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:21,200
 I saw that bastard looking at my wife lovingly and yet... 

96
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,020
Min Seok!

97
00:08:23,020 --> 00:08:25,810
-  H-Hey, Jun Hui. 
 -  I didn't have any doubts. 

98
00:08:25,810 --> 00:08:31,080
 I was talking to Mi Jin about the menu for the camping this weekend. 

99
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:33,940
Oh, Honey? I must've fallen asleep.

100
00:08:33,940 --> 00:08:36,110
 It's quite late now. Go to sleep now. 

101
00:08:36,110 --> 00:08:37,940
 I'll see you at the camp. 

102
00:08:37,940 --> 00:08:40,170
Y-Yes, Hyeong.

103
00:08:40,170 --> 00:08:43,870
 We didn't even know that and went camping together every weekend 

104
00:08:43,870 --> 00:08:47,110
 like complete morons. 

105
00:08:47,110 --> 00:08:49,270
 Those evil bastards. 

106
00:08:49,270 --> 00:08:52,490
Here's your meat.

107
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:54,520
Right?

108
00:08:55,230 --> 00:08:57,070
All right. Pass them down.

109
00:08:57,070 --> 00:08:58,120
It's orange!

110
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,700
- Pass them down.
 - Pass them down.

111
00:08:59,700 --> 00:09:02,890
Mom, can I have one glass of Sprite before I eat the orange?

112
00:09:02,890 --> 00:09:04,100
You can't have Sprite.

113
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:07,170
- Come on. Just one! 
- No, I said you can't have Sprite.

114
00:09:07,170 --> 00:09:10,400
- Drink water.
 - Seung Wu, you want Sprite?

115
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,150
Should we have some Sprite just for today?

116
00:09:12,150 --> 00:09:14,070
- Should I give you some? 
- You can't.

117
00:09:14,070 --> 00:09:16,280
Come on. We're camping.

118
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:19,020
Gosh, this is when he gets some.

119
00:09:19,020 --> 00:09:21,110
- Just for today since we're camping. 
- Okay.

120
00:09:21,110 --> 00:09:23,710
Dad's the best, right?

121
00:09:24,470 --> 00:09:27,840
Here's the Sprite Seung Wu loves.

122
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:30,430
All right. Moms can take the kids and go inside the RVs.

123
00:09:30,430 --> 00:09:32,720
Dads will finish cleaning here.

124
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:36,470
Hyeongnim, what should we do? Our RV's heater isn't working.

125
00:09:36,470 --> 00:09:37,890
Really?

126
00:09:37,890 --> 00:09:41,360
It'll be a lot colder later at night.

127
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:48,420
Let's all just sleep together in our RV.

128
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:52,370
Shall we? But we'd be really intruding.

129
00:09:52,370 --> 00:09:54,810
No need to say that when we're like family.

130
00:09:54,810 --> 00:09:56,610
Here's good news for you kids.

131
00:09:56,610 --> 00:09:59,990
You'll all be sleeping together today!

132
00:09:59,990 --> 00:10:02,230
- Let's go inside now.
 - Let's go!

133
00:10:02,230 --> 00:10:04,150
All right, now. Let's go.

134
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:07,350
Come on. Go inside.

135
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:28,580
Gosh, did I drink too much water?

136
00:11:25,340 --> 00:11:28,380
 I thought I was in hell. 

137
00:11:29,770 --> 00:11:33,750
 I should've killed those bastards on the spot. 

138
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:40,010
 Who knew those fingers 

139
00:11:41,190 --> 00:11:44,660
 were really that bitch's fingers. 

140
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:54,080
The puzzle was completed when we put the pieces together later.

141
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:59,900
I asked myself a hundred times whether I should tell him or not.

142
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:02,060
It hurts so much I can die,

143
00:12:02,060 --> 00:12:05,820
but should I let my friend feel the same pain?

144
00:12:05,820 --> 00:12:10,590
But not telling him would be an even worse thing to do.

145
00:12:20,220 --> 00:12:22,500
Did your wife admit to it?

146
00:12:22,500 --> 00:12:25,160
At first, she said it was nonsense.

147
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:28,620
But I showed her the CCTV footage, and she admitted it.

148
00:12:28,620 --> 00:12:30,730
I also recorded her.

149
00:12:31,780 --> 00:12:33,980
Do you have additional evidence, Kim Min Jeong?

150
00:12:33,980 --> 00:12:38,810
Yes, I captured the pictures of when they went away by themselves

151
00:12:38,810 --> 00:12:42,510
and their messages that are on his phone.

152
00:12:42,510 --> 00:12:46,040
Since you secured the evidence well, it'll go well.

153
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:48,220
Your husband is quite rich, Kim Min Jeong.

154
00:12:48,220 --> 00:12:50,280
We'll need to make him pay a lot.

155
00:12:50,280 --> 00:12:53,460
It's mostly from his father, so would it be possible?

156
00:12:53,460 --> 00:12:56,210
Since his father has a reputation as an assemblyman,

157
00:12:56,210 --> 00:12:58,760
I'll attempt a mediation.

158
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:04,000
A case where Kim Min Jeong is the plaintiff, and

159
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,220
another case where Kim Jun Hui is the plaintiff.

160
00:13:06,220 --> 00:13:09,670
We'll be proceeding with two lawsuits that way.

161
00:13:10,570 --> 00:13:12,780
Let's make it a success.

162
00:13:13,780 --> 00:13:15,240
Yes.

163
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:23,190
All right, all right. Here's your tteokbokki.

164
00:13:23,190 --> 00:13:24,740
Give it a try.

165
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:26,630
It's just kimbap (seaweed rice roll) and tteokbokki?

166
00:13:26,630 --> 00:13:29,110
"Just"? This place is a really hip place.

167
00:13:29,110 --> 00:13:30,550
It's hard to get a table here.

168
00:13:30,550 --> 00:13:35,370
I went through so much to get a seat by the window here. Seriously.

169
00:13:36,850 --> 00:13:40,080
Try this, too. This is really delicious.

170
00:13:45,260 --> 00:13:49,170
Is it because I ate something delicious? I do feel a bit better.

171
00:13:49,170 --> 00:13:51,740
It's delicious, right? I told you.

172
00:13:52,390 --> 00:13:55,950
To be honest, I was on the job site yesterday.

173
00:13:55,950 --> 00:13:57,990
The job site— You can't.

174
00:13:57,990 --> 00:13:59,720
Did you forget our company is a major law firm?

175
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:01,450
It's so hard to get hired.

176
00:14:01,450 --> 00:14:05,250
But it's a waste to quit right away like this.

177
00:14:06,190 --> 00:14:10,410
Attorney Jeon, do you enjoy being a divorce attorney?

178
00:14:11,420 --> 00:14:14,680
Since you started working three months before me, tell me how you feel.

179
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:18,460
What's this? How did you know I'm your senior by three months? My cover is blown.

180
00:14:18,460 --> 00:14:19,210
My cover is blown.

181
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:23,400
I thought you were my senior by a few years because you acted like that.

182
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:26,480
Come on. I'm still your senior, even if by three months.

183
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:29,870
I honestly applied, thinking divorce cases would be fun.

184
00:14:29,870 --> 00:14:32,880
I love watching dramas, you see. Especially melodramas.

185
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:35,650
You joined the Divorce Team because you like melodramas?

186
00:14:35,650 --> 00:14:37,370
Yes, they're funny.

187
00:14:37,370 --> 00:14:40,850
There's all these headaches in mergers and criminal litigations,

188
00:14:40,850 --> 00:14:44,320
doing all that research and looking for precedents. Just thinking about it gives me a headache.

189
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:48,150
Wow.  I found those way more interesting.

190
00:14:48,150 --> 00:14:50,480
 She's so confident. 

191
00:14:50,480 --> 00:14:52,650
 You're so great, huh? 

192
00:14:52,650 --> 00:14:56,620
By the way, Hoobaenim, you're starting to skip the honorifics now, huh?

193
00:14:56,620 --> 00:14:59,660
Is it because we graduated the same year?

194
00:14:59,660 --> 00:15:03,460
We were in the same class, so I could skip the honorifics from now on, right?

195
00:15:03,460 --> 00:15:05,710
It does feel a bit early, but...

196
00:15:05,710 --> 00:15:08,990
Fine. If you can have a comfortable time at work

197
00:15:08,990 --> 00:15:12,260
by skipping the honorifics for me, have it your way.

198
00:15:12,260 --> 00:15:14,550
Attorney Han, please don't leave.

199
00:15:14,550 --> 00:15:17,430
You don't know how many people came and left in the last three months, right?

200
00:15:17,430 --> 00:15:20,990
 Why is he clinging to me like a puppy? 

201
00:15:20,990 --> 00:15:23,970
If the attorney in charge was changed that often,

202
00:15:23,970 --> 00:15:25,580
the clients must've had a lot of complaints.

203
00:15:25,580 --> 00:15:28,720
It was no joke. That's why Attorney Cha was really busy.

204
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:31,060
She was doing sales here and taking care of complaints there.

205
00:15:31,060 --> 00:15:32,960
She went to the provinces and attended all the trials alone.

206
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:36,890
I couldn't help but respect her from deep inside.

207
00:15:37,460 --> 00:15:42,300
But Attorney Cha's daughter would only get to see her mom's face on TV.

208
00:15:42,850 --> 00:15:47,010
Gosh, did he cheat on his wife because she's too busy?

209
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:53,570
Attorney Han, don't be like that. Hang in there for just one more month.

210
00:15:53,570 --> 00:15:56,360
Our lunch is covered by our company,

211
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:58,160
so I'll buy you all the coffee you need.

212
00:15:58,160 --> 00:16:00,660
Gosh, it's fine. Why would you buy me coffee?

213
00:16:00,660 --> 00:16:02,990
I just want to buy it for you.

214
00:16:02,990 --> 00:16:05,140
What's gotten into you?

215
00:16:05,140 --> 00:16:07,790
- Are you interested in me?
 - What?

216
00:16:07,790 --> 00:16:10,980
Love your colleague and your country.

217
00:16:12,170 --> 00:16:14,010
Don't you know?

218
00:16:14,010 --> 00:16:16,300
Go on. Help yourself.

219
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:19,080
Endure just one more month. Okay?

220
00:16:30,230 --> 00:16:33,320
Attorney Han, are you working late today?

221
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:35,860
Yes, I still have things to review.

222
00:16:35,860 --> 00:16:38,430
We'll go ahead and leave, then.

223
00:16:40,590 --> 00:16:43,430
Oh, yes. Take care.

224
00:16:44,750 --> 00:16:46,360
Let's go.

225
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:48,260
- Get home safe.
 - You, too.

226
00:16:48,260 --> 00:16:50,040
Take care.

227
00:16:57,040 --> 00:16:58,960
All right. Let's go in.

228
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:02,670
Hello. Boss, do you have a table?

229
00:17:04,910 --> 00:17:06,180
What is it?

230
00:17:06,180 --> 00:17:09,120
You always ate the basic kimbap to save time.

231
00:17:09,120 --> 00:17:11,460
What made you order tteokbokki as well today?

232
00:17:11,460 --> 00:17:14,380
And a spicy tteokbokki, on top of that.

233
00:17:16,550 --> 00:17:18,510
Tell me.

234
00:17:20,510 --> 00:17:22,210
It's not like that. This place is just good.

235
00:17:22,210 --> 00:17:26,900
It can't be what I'm thinking, right?

236
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:29,520
- Not yet.
 - Not yet?

237
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:48,400
 I thought she was working late, but she was compositing a letter of resignation. 

238
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,290
Again?

239
00:17:49,290 --> 00:17:54,200
She thinks listening to people venting is what a divorce case is.

240
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:55,540
I don't think she'll last long.

241
00:17:55,540 --> 00:17:58,190
What about a 20% pay raise?

242
00:17:58,190 --> 00:18:03,630
I'm not sure if she can be controlled with money.

243
00:18:05,370 --> 00:18:08,920
From what I saw back then, she felt uneasy even after winning her first case.

244
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:11,130
Could that be the reason?

245
00:18:11,830 --> 00:18:15,030
Comfort her a bit if she says she's quitting.

246
00:18:15,030 --> 00:18:18,270
No, thanks. Why would I go that far?

247
00:18:19,310 --> 00:18:22,730
I just won't give Han Yu Ri the chance to talk about it.

248
00:18:22,730 --> 00:18:26,560
Seonbae, if I weren't here, there'd be no one who'd tell you these things.

249
00:18:26,560 --> 00:18:29,450
Don't be too harsh on the kids.

250
00:18:29,450 --> 00:18:32,180
And stop making enemies.

251
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:35,250
What's this, Attorney Jeong? Are you going somewhere?

252
00:18:35,250 --> 00:18:37,560
Where would I go?

253
00:18:39,470 --> 00:18:40,650
 In session 

